q.q:
In particular Herr Strauss and Mr. Sandys agreed:


(1) that there should be a full exchange of technical information on the tanks at present under development in the two countries and that each should make prototypes available to the other for test and study, with the aim of evolving common solutions to the tactical and technical problems of development and production;



(2) that, subject to further study the two countries would endeavour to agree on the adoption of a standardised family of light tracked military vehicles;

(3) that, subject to further discussion of the technical issues involved, the two countries should co-operate in the development of advanced anti-tank guided weapons and that other countries already engaged in this type of work should be invited to associate themselves with this effort.
